 thatpost-conflict reconstruction is a highly gendered process,demonstrating that a clear recognition and understandingof the roles and experiences of female soldiers are centralto both understanding the conflict and to crafting effectivepolicy for the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPostwar reconstructionxSierra Leone. 0aPostwar reconstructionzSierra Leone. 0aRape as a weapon of warxSierra Leone. 0aRape as a weapon of warzSierra Leone. 0aSex rolexSierra Leone. 0aSex rolezSierra Leone. 0aWomen soldiersxSierra Leone. 0aWomen soldierszSierra Leone. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aSylvester, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081476137340uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814761373.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814771259423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814771259/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK